    <a name="defining-the-vision"></a><h2>Defining the Vision</h2>
    <h3>If team administration was a house: User management and access visibility would be the foundation.</h3>
    <p>While automating the sharing process was a worthy endeavour, there were other more pressing issues that needed to be addressed first. As such, Dylan and I put together the following recommendations for holistically improving Team Administration within iAuditor.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Milestone 1: User Management</strong><br/>
      Improve onboarding; visibility; and management of users within an organisation.</li>
      <li><strong>Milestone 2: Group Management</strong><br/>
      Easier setup; visibility; and management of groups within an organisation.</li>
      <li><strong>Milestone 3: Sharing Workflows</strong><br/>
      Reusable sharing patterns that work.</li>
      <li><strong>Milestone 4: Delegated Privileges/Hierarchy</strong><br/>
      Privilege delegation; organisational control; automated sharing patterns; and simplified permissions.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Milestones 1 and 2 would see the introduction of user and group profiles into iAuditor. Solving the visibility and management issues, while providing a foundation for an improved sharing experience.</p>
