    <a name="pitching-the-vision"></a><h2>Pitching the Vision</h2>
    <h3>The key to successfully pitching our vision hung on our ability to effectively communicate the pain experienced daily by our customers.</h3>
    <p>We had to pitch our recommendations to various stakeholders, including the:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Product Manager for the Team Management Team</li>
      <li>Heads of Product, Design, Customer Support and Customer Success</li>
      <li>Team Management Team</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Our pitch detailed each of the four milestones, and for each milestone we:</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Discussed the high-level problem that required addressing.</li>
      <li>Provided compelling and memorable customer stories that represented significant portions of our user base.</li>
      <li>Summarised what we aspired to accomplish.</li>
      <li>Showcased early design mocks and prototypes to aid in outcome visualisations.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To ensure everyone walked away from our pitch understanding our customers' frustrations, we ran activities we called "Feel the customer pain". Participants would be assigned a series of tasks that our customers regularly do; tasks that are either impossible; too time-consuming; or confusing.</p>
